                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1219" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1219" type="surname" value="TRINDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1219" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390204-744-offence-1 t18390204-name-1219"></join>William Trinder</persName>; and that Pitman had before been convicted of felony.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1220" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1220" type="surname" value="ANTHONY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1220" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE ANTHONY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a writer—on the 11th of January I saw the two prisoners together, about eleven o'clock in the morning, in Whitcombe-street—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183902040184"></xptr>
               <p>watched them for about five minutes, and about half-past one o'clock I met them in Grafton-street—I then saw that Johnston had got Pitman's apron with something in it—I followed him to the private door of Mr. Wadmore, a pawnbroker (Pitman was on the other side of the way)—I went in at the shop door, and told the shopkeeper—he produced this caddy to me—I said, "That has been stolen; detain it and the party"—I got a policeman and sent him to the shop—I followed Pitman down Tottenham Court-road, where he was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1221" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1221" type="surname" value="KILSSY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1221" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY KILSSY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Tottenham Court-road—I am a pawnbroker—Johnston offered me this caddy—the witness told me to detain him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1222" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1222" type="surname" value="TRINDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390204-name-1222" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM TRINDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Whitcombe-street—this is my caddy, and was on a table in my shop, which is open-fronted.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Pitman.</hi> It was outside instead of in.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Johnston's Defence.</hi> We were out of work, and forced to sleep in the street two nights before this, and seeing this outside we were tempted to take it—we had nothing to eat.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390204-name-1223" type="witnessName">
